				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">They should take a page fom the WotC book on how to handle it:
<br />

<br />
1. don't restrict classes by race.
<br />
2. Allow for someone to multiclass (choose a new class at each level if they desire).
<br />
3. Make classes with prerequisites that a character needs to achieve to get a level in that class, ala <span style="font-style: italic">prestige</span> or <span style="font-style: italic">advanced</span> classes.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Then people could have much more flexability in their characters, and produce real unique styles.  It also gives the feeling of having more control over their characters, and could attract more interest in the game.  It's also most likely, due to the nature of EQ, never, <span style="font-style: italic">ever</span> going to happen.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: blue"><span style="font-weight: bold">"I'm not responcabel fer my comuter's spleling errnors."</span></span>
<br />
     - Xlorep DarkHelm</span>
